{"word":"G3795 - ὀψάριον - opsárion - op-sar'-ee-on - Fish","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὀψάριον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">opsárion</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">op-sar'-ee-on</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Fish</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Noun Neuter / பெயர்ச்சொல் (அஃறிணை)</span>"},{"paragraph":"மீன் - பால் வேறுபாடற்ற பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":"fish"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Neuter of a presumed derivative of the base of <a href=\"#/G3702 - ὀπτός - optós - op-tos'/3702\">G3702</a>; a <i>relish</i> to other food (as if cooked <i>sauce</i>), that is, (specifically) <i>fish</i> (presumably salted and dried as a condiment): - fish.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}